cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.AI, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a translation from linear temporal logic (LTL) to deterministic Emerson-Lei automata, which are omega-automata with a Muller acceptance condition. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of the translation in the tool Delag. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with automata and their acceptance conditions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is possible as the paper mentions probabilistic model checking case studies. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also possible as the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of the translation in a tool.
